Instance Variables:
These are declared inside the class and not inside method

Properties of instance variables
=> They always get a default value
=> Cannot be reinitialized directly within a class

Static Variables:
Are declared within class using static keyword
Properties of static variable
Only one copy is created per class
we don't need an object to access the static variable

Local variables:
These are declared in methods or method parameters.
Properties of local variables.
 Cannot be accessed outside methods.
